1
00:00:10,300 --> 00:00:11,567
<i> Captain!</i>

2
00:00:11,700 --> 00:00:12,767
<i>- Hello?
- Mar!</i>

3
00:00:12,900 --> 00:00:14,267
<i> Listen to me first!</i>

4
00:00:14,400 --> 00:00:15,367
<i> Mariano?</i>

5
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:17,767
<i> Who are you?</i>

6
00:00:17,900 --> 00:00:19,467
<i> Donabel Mae Custudio!</i>

7
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:20,500
<i> Donabel?</i>

8
00:00:20,633 --> 00:00:23,367
<i>Your one and only ex
from high school!</i>

9
00:00:23,500 --> 00:00:24,967
<i> Spend time with your family.</i>

10
00:00:25,100 --> 00:00:27,500
<i>I know your job
is important to you,</i>

11
00:00:27,633 --> 00:00:31,000
<i>but what's more important
than family?</i>

12
00:00:31,133 --> 00:00:31,967
<i> Ma'am, you're right.</i>

13
00:00:32,100 --> 00:00:33,600
<i> Chief, I've made my decision.</i>

14
00:00:33,767 --> 00:00:34,867
<i> I'm resigning, Chief.</i>

15
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:36,233
<i> Bobby, just a moment.</i>

16
00:00:36,367 --> 00:00:38,533
<i>Tonyo, why are you meddling
in my life?</i>

17
00:00:38,667 --> 00:00:40,767
<i>Bobby, just a moment,
it's not like that.</i>

18
00:00:40,900 --> 00:00:43,800
<i>Bobby, is Lieutenant Conde
bothering you?</i>

19
00:00:43,933 --> 00:00:44,800
<i> No, Mayor.</i>

20
00:00:44,933 --> 00:00:45,800
<i>Let's pretend you have
a girlfriend,</i>

21
00:00:45,933 --> 00:00:47,033
<i>and she wants to join the
pageant.</i>

22
00:00:47,167 --> 00:00:48,167
<i>What, you'll let her join
or not?</i>

23
00:00:48,300 --> 00:00:49,333
<i> I'll support her</i>

24
00:00:49,467 --> 00:00:50,567
<i> in whatever she wants, even...</i>

25
00:00:50,700 --> 00:00:53,333
<i>even if I don't want to,
if that's what makes her happy.</i>

26
00:00:53,467 --> 00:00:54,433
<i> Hello, Peach?</i>

27
00:00:54,567 --> 00:00:55,667
<i> Okay, I'm not joining anymore.</i>

28
00:00:55,800 --> 00:00:56,767
<i> Take care and do your best.</i>

29
00:00:56,900 --> 00:00:58,033
<i> But you saw it, Boss,</i>

30
00:00:58,167 --> 00:00:59,700
<i> one shot, one kill.</i>

31
00:00:59,833 --> 00:01:03,567
<i>Maybe I can ask for a little
bonus for that?</i>

32
00:01:03,700 --> 00:01:06,000
<i>Next time, when everything
is ironed out.</i>

33
00:01:06,133 --> 00:01:07,267
<i>Right now, someone is still
looking for</i>

34
00:01:07,433 --> 00:01:10,700
<i>who ordered
Lieutenant Robles's death.</i>

35
00:01:10,833 --> 00:01:12,733
<i> Who among them?</i>

36
00:01:12,867 --> 00:01:14,033
<i> It's Conde.</i>

37
00:01:14,167 --> 00:01:17,400
You know, I've been suspecting
for a long time that you're gay.

38
00:01:17,533 --> 00:01:19,533
You're even my mom's favorite.

39
00:01:19,667 --> 00:01:21,200
I just can't tell her

40
00:01:21,333 --> 00:01:23,267
that there's something wrong
with you.

41
00:01:23,400 --> 00:01:26,167
You know, Donabel,
I'm really sorry, huh?

42
00:01:26,300 --> 00:01:28,233
Because...

43
00:01:28,367 --> 00:01:30,900
the reason I courted you is...

44
00:01:31,033 --> 00:01:32,400
oh...

45
00:01:32,533 --> 00:01:35,133
that I'm eyeing your eyebrows.

46
00:01:35,267 --> 00:01:38,833
It's so nice to pluck and shave.

47
00:01:38,967 --> 00:01:42,233
And your makeup
was expensive before.

48
00:01:42,400 --> 00:01:44,200
Wait! You mean,
you're the one who's using up

49
00:01:44,333 --> 00:01:47,067
my makeup and blush on?

50
00:01:47,200 --> 00:01:48,300
Sorry, girl.

51
00:01:48,433 --> 00:01:51,267
Of course, it's imported.

52
00:01:51,400 --> 00:01:55,200
And if I had known you were
joining a beauty pageant,

53
00:01:55,333 --> 00:01:58,667
I wouldn't have applied
to be your PA.

54
00:01:58,800 --> 00:01:59,700
You know,

55
00:01:59,833 --> 00:02:02,300
I want that kind of sideline,
right?

56
00:02:02,433 --> 00:02:04,667
Do you want to?
Do you want to be my PA?

57
00:02:04,800 --> 00:02:08,267
Because I'm going to join
Miss Calabari again.

58
00:02:08,400 --> 00:02:10,833
They're accepting
application again.

59
00:02:10,967 --> 00:02:11,933
Wait...

60
00:02:12,067 --> 00:02:13,233
How many times have you joined?

61
00:02:13,367 --> 00:02:14,367
Just a few!

62
00:02:14,533 --> 00:02:16,633
Like, five.

63
00:02:16,767 --> 00:02:18,333
Five!

64
00:02:18,467 --> 00:02:20,467
Your faith is strong, isn't it?

65
00:02:20,600 --> 00:02:24,067
I'm not winning,
so I keep on competing!

66
00:02:24,200 --> 00:02:25,967
Oh, wait...

67
00:02:26,100 --> 00:02:29,833
if you're not participating
in the pageant,

68
00:02:29,967 --> 00:02:30,933
what do you do?

69
00:02:31,067 --> 00:02:33,900
Just at home,
gardening, cooking.

70
00:02:34,033 --> 00:02:37,967
But lately, I've been training
pageant contestants.

71
00:02:38,100 --> 00:02:41,467
You know, they want to train in
makeup, how to walk.

72
00:02:41,600 --> 00:02:42,567
Overall training.

73
00:02:42,700 --> 00:02:44,100
So if you know someone there,

74
00:02:44,233 --> 00:02:45,200
refer them to me.

75
00:02:47,633 --> 00:02:48,767
Mar.

76
00:02:49,633 --> 00:02:50,367
Mar.

77
00:02:50,500 --> 00:02:51,433
Oh...

78
00:02:51,567 --> 00:02:53,533
Oh, Bobby...

79
00:02:53,667 --> 00:02:55,133
Oh...

80
00:02:55,267 --> 00:02:57,700
This is Donabel.

81
00:02:57,833 --> 00:02:59,300
- Donabel.
- Oh, hi, Donabel.

82
00:02:59,433 --> 00:03:00,733
- Nice to meet you.
- She's my...

83
00:03:00,867 --> 00:03:02,467
ex in high school.

84
00:03:02,600 --> 00:03:03,700
Not just an ex.

85
00:03:03,833 --> 00:03:06,233
I was Mariano's first kiss
in high school.

86
00:03:07,433 --> 00:03:08,233
Hey...

87
00:03:09,067 --> 00:03:11,467
Hey, okay, maybe you guys
are still talking.

88
00:03:11,600 --> 00:03:13,433
- I'll go ahead.
- Oh, no, Bobby.

89
00:03:13,567 --> 00:03:15,167
I'll go with you.

90
00:03:15,300 --> 00:03:17,667
Oh, Donabel, I'm sorry,

91
00:03:17,800 --> 00:03:18,833
but I need to go.

92
00:03:18,967 --> 00:03:20,767
Oh, okay, let's just talk soon.

93
00:03:20,933 --> 00:03:22,200
Come visit me at home, okay?

94
00:03:22,333 --> 00:03:22,900
Sure, yes.

95
00:03:23,033 --> 00:03:24,067
- Promise?
- Yes.

96
00:03:25,533 --> 00:03:26,967
Oh, okay.

97
00:03:27,100 --> 00:03:28,767
- I'm sorry, huh? Okay.
- Okay.

98
00:03:28,900 --> 00:03:29,867
- Bye.
- Take care.

99
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:31,133
Let's go, Bobby.

100
00:03:31,267 --> 00:03:32,200
What's that?

101
00:03:32,333 --> 00:03:33,667
Is that really your ex?

102
00:03:33,800 --> 00:03:36,033
Wow, she's so beautiful
and tall,

103
00:03:36,167 --> 00:03:38,733
just like Abdul, oh, oh.

104
00:03:38,867 --> 00:03:40,500
And Mar...

105
00:03:40,633 --> 00:03:41,533
What?

106
00:03:41,667 --> 00:03:43,700
You can't believe that
she was my first kiss?

107
00:03:43,833 --> 00:03:44,867
No.

108
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:46,400
I can't believe...

109
00:03:46,533 --> 00:03:48,333
your name is Mariano.

110
00:03:48,467 --> 00:03:50,000
- I didn't hear anything, Bobby!
- Hey, Mariano!

111
00:03:50,133 --> 00:03:52,000
Was she really your first kiss?

112
00:04:19,800 --> 00:04:21,400
Abdul!

113
00:04:21,533 --> 00:04:24,533
Grandma! We're home!

114
00:04:28,200 --> 00:04:29,833
Oh, Abdul!

115
00:04:29,967 --> 00:04:32,233
Who did this to you?

116
00:04:32,367 --> 00:04:34,500
Who oppressed you?

117
00:04:34,633 --> 00:04:36,667
- Bobby! Bobby!
- Oh?

118
00:04:36,800 --> 00:04:37,833
Oh? Why?
What?

119
00:04:37,967 --> 00:04:38,467
Abdul!

120
00:04:39,733 --> 00:04:41,567
Who did this?

121
00:04:41,700 --> 00:04:42,800
Grandma...

122
00:04:42,933 --> 00:04:44,233
Bobby, don't!

123
00:04:45,267 --> 00:04:47,000
Your Grandma is in a state
of calamity.

124
00:04:47,133 --> 00:04:48,933
She did this!

125
00:04:49,067 --> 00:04:51,267
She doesn't recognize
anyone anymore

126
00:04:51,400 --> 00:04:52,433
Look.

127
00:04:52,567 --> 00:04:55,900
She tied me up and then
threatened me with a bolo!

128
00:04:56,033 --> 00:04:57,233
What?

129
00:04:57,367 --> 00:04:59,767
With your size, Abdul,
Captain tied you up?

130
00:04:59,900 --> 00:05:01,567
Are you stupid?

131
00:05:01,733 --> 00:05:03,200
She doesn't know me.

132
00:05:03,333 --> 00:05:05,133
Can you untie my rope?

133
00:05:05,267 --> 00:05:06,400
What is that?
Can't you take it off?

134
00:05:06,533 --> 00:05:07,433
No!

135
00:05:07,567 --> 00:05:09,033
It's a good thing
you called earlier.

136
00:05:09,167 --> 00:05:10,533
This is so tight!

137
00:05:11,833 --> 00:05:13,267
Grandma...

138
00:05:16,900 --> 00:05:18,533
Grandma...

139
00:05:22,600 --> 00:05:23,700
Bobby...

140
00:05:23,833 --> 00:05:26,033
it's good
you came home early.

141
00:05:26,167 --> 00:05:27,333
Grandma...

142
00:05:27,467 --> 00:05:29,800
why did you tie
Abdul up?

143
00:05:31,467 --> 00:05:32,733
Tied him up?

144
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:40,267
Why would I tie him up?

145
00:05:41,767 --> 00:05:43,600
Hey, Abdul!

146
00:05:43,733 --> 00:05:46,167
What are you saying
I tied you up?

147
00:05:47,200 --> 00:05:49,633
You are making up stories.

148
00:05:57,900 --> 00:05:59,133
Grandma...

149
00:05:59,267 --> 00:06:01,567
Grandma, I'm coming in.

150
00:06:03,200 --> 00:06:04,700
Grandchild...

151
00:06:07,500 --> 00:06:10,500
Grandma, why are you doing
laundry here?

152
00:06:11,833 --> 00:06:13,533
Laundry?

153
00:06:13,667 --> 00:06:15,400
I'm not doing laundry.

154
00:06:18,533 --> 00:06:20,633
I didn't bring that in.

155
00:06:20,767 --> 00:06:22,000
Maybe it's Mar.

156
00:06:28,400 --> 00:06:30,367
Oh...

157
00:06:30,500 --> 00:06:31,833
Grandma...

158
00:06:31,967 --> 00:06:33,667
come here first.

159
00:06:33,800 --> 00:06:35,167
Oh...

160
00:06:42,267 --> 00:06:43,433
Grandma...

161
00:06:44,433 --> 00:06:46,500
There's...

162
00:06:46,633 --> 00:06:48,967
something you need to know.

163
00:06:50,833 --> 00:06:51,933
Know?

164
00:06:52,067 --> 00:06:53,900
What's that?

165
00:06:58,000 --> 00:06:59,933
You are sick.

166
00:07:03,133 --> 00:07:04,800
Am I sick?

167
00:07:07,067 --> 00:07:09,067
What are you saying?

168
00:07:09,200 --> 00:07:10,667
What's wrong with me?

169
00:07:13,300 --> 00:07:14,800
Oh...

170
00:07:16,067 --> 00:07:19,633
Grandma, you're starting
to have dementia.

171
00:07:21,967 --> 00:07:23,567
Dementia...

172
00:07:23,700 --> 00:07:25,667
Isn't that...

173
00:07:25,800 --> 00:07:27,600
in the brain,
in the mind?

174
00:07:29,667 --> 00:07:30,767
Yes, Grandma.

175
00:07:31,967 --> 00:07:34,833
That's why there are things
and people

176
00:07:34,967 --> 00:07:36,667
that you can't remember.

177
00:07:42,933 --> 00:07:44,400
What?

178
00:07:45,967 --> 00:07:47,600
What's happening to me?

179
00:07:49,033 --> 00:07:50,833
Did I do something

180
00:07:50,967 --> 00:07:52,967
to get this disease?

181
00:07:54,300 --> 00:07:56,100
Grandma, you didn't do anything.

182
00:07:57,267 --> 00:07:59,333
You're not the only one
experiencing this.

183
00:08:00,533 --> 00:08:02,033
But, Grandma...

184
00:08:02,167 --> 00:08:04,067
don't worry...

185
00:08:05,367 --> 00:08:09,733
because Mar, Abdul, and I
are here to take care of you.

186
00:08:10,800 --> 00:08:13,300
Just don't tie him up
again, okay?

187
00:08:14,533 --> 00:08:16,667
How about your job, Bobby?

188
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:19,233
Oh...

189
00:08:20,400 --> 00:08:23,733
I was planning to take a break

190
00:08:23,900 --> 00:08:26,033
so I could take care of you.

191
00:08:28,733 --> 00:08:30,400
Bobby...

192
00:08:30,533 --> 00:08:33,467
that's something
you shouldn't do.

193
00:08:36,467 --> 00:08:39,200
But, Grandma, it's okay.

194
00:08:39,333 --> 00:08:41,333
It's okay with me.

195
00:08:43,667 --> 00:08:45,900
It's not okay with me.

196
00:08:46,933 --> 00:08:48,733
Even if my memory fades,

197
00:08:49,800 --> 00:08:50,433
I want...

198
00:08:51,367 --> 00:08:53,833
the last image I have of you...

199
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:56,967
is you wearing
your police uniform,

200
00:08:59,867 --> 00:09:02,633
happily pursuing your dreams.

201
00:09:28,367 --> 00:09:29,967
Abdul, I'm sorry.

202
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:32,033
That's okay, girl

203
00:09:32,167 --> 00:09:33,367
That'll go away.

204
00:09:33,500 --> 00:09:35,467
Hey, friend, have a glass
of water first.

205
00:09:35,600 --> 00:09:36,633
Hey, that's sweet,
isn't it, Mar?

206
00:09:36,767 --> 00:09:37,567
That's just for now.

207
00:09:37,700 --> 00:09:39,300
Thank you.

208
00:09:39,433 --> 00:09:40,367
So Bobby, what's your decision?

209
00:09:40,500 --> 00:09:43,700
Oh, resign or not to resign?

210
00:09:44,633 --> 00:09:47,167
Actually, I'm still thinking
about it.

211
00:09:47,300 --> 00:09:51,267
But I already told Chief that
I'm resigning.

212
00:09:51,400 --> 00:09:52,333
You haven't given him

213
00:09:52,467 --> 00:09:54,767
a resignation letter yet,
have you?

214
00:09:54,900 --> 00:09:56,467
That's not final yet.

215
00:09:56,600 --> 00:09:57,767
That's your water, right?

216
00:09:57,900 --> 00:09:59,133
Oh, sorry.

217
00:09:59,267 --> 00:10:00,733
Sorry, sorry, Mar.

218
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:03,733
And what about Grandma?

219
00:10:04,833 --> 00:10:06,600
You won't leave her
completely, right?

220
00:10:06,733 --> 00:10:09,633
Besides, I know, in Captain's
cases,

221
00:10:09,767 --> 00:10:11,733
there really are caregivers.

222
00:10:12,900 --> 00:10:15,100
It's Donabel!

223
00:10:15,233 --> 00:10:17,067
-Do you know that I was tied up?
-Oh, sorry.

224
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:19,200
- Have you been tied up before?
- Sorry.

225
00:10:19,333 --> 00:10:21,433
- Sorry, sorry.
- Okay, that's your last, okay?

226
00:10:21,567 --> 00:10:23,900
- It hurts.
- There you go, Donabel,

227
00:10:24,033 --> 00:10:25,933
the one I introduced to you
to earlier.

228
00:10:26,067 --> 00:10:28,733
She mentioned that she used
to be a caregiver

229
00:10:28,867 --> 00:10:30,167
at a home for the aged

230
00:10:30,300 --> 00:10:33,167
before she started
doing beauty pageants.

231
00:10:33,300 --> 00:10:36,200
Maybe she can refer us
to someone.

232
00:10:36,367 --> 00:10:38,167
So, how was the last encounter?

233
00:10:38,300 --> 00:10:39,533
Was there a spark?

234
00:10:39,667 --> 00:10:40,900
Joke!

235
00:10:41,033 --> 00:10:42,300
We're just friends now!

236
00:10:42,433 --> 00:10:43,633
If I hit you, let's see!

237
00:10:43,767 --> 00:10:46,067
Sorry, we're just friends now.

238
00:10:46,200 --> 00:10:48,000
You know, I was wondering
about her.

239
00:10:48,133 --> 00:10:49,467
She has no job,

240
00:10:49,600 --> 00:10:51,300
just participating
in beauty pageants,

241
00:10:51,433 --> 00:10:52,900
beauty contest,

242
00:10:53,033 --> 00:10:54,567
but she's sophisticated.

243
00:10:54,700 --> 00:10:57,233
The clothes she wears
are expensive.

244
00:10:57,367 --> 00:10:59,067
I don't know how
she can afford them.

245
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:00,900
Maybe she's
the Mayor's mistress!

246
00:11:01,033 --> 00:11:03,600
Hey, you two,
you're creating intrigues.

247
00:11:03,733 --> 00:11:07,500
Oh well, I'll eventually find
out who her sugar daddy is,

248
00:11:07,667 --> 00:11:11,067
because she allowed me
to be her PA.

249
00:11:11,200 --> 00:11:12,533
- Right?
- Oh, really?

250
00:11:12,667 --> 00:11:13,267
Yes!

251
00:11:14,233 --> 00:11:16,100
Extra income.

252
00:11:17,400 --> 00:11:18,367
Oh!

253
00:11:18,500 --> 00:11:21,067
Speaking of my ex

254
00:11:21,200 --> 00:11:22,733
she sent me a message.

255
00:11:22,867 --> 00:11:23,667
Oh.

256
00:11:23,800 --> 00:11:26,067
Let's go to her house.

257
00:11:26,200 --> 00:11:29,433
There's wine, food,
and chit chat!

258
00:11:29,567 --> 00:11:31,200
Come on, exciting!

259
00:11:34,967 --> 00:11:36,800
<i> After one week...</i>

260
00:11:36,933 --> 00:11:39,433
Chief is about to be discharged.

261
00:11:39,567 --> 00:11:42,400
I'm sure he'll be reporting
to the precinct right away.

262
00:11:42,567 --> 00:11:44,133
Torres, De Jesus...

263
00:11:44,267 --> 00:11:45,833
just because Chief is gone,

264
00:11:45,967 --> 00:11:47,400
our world will stop, okay?

265
00:11:47,533 --> 00:11:49,900
What's the news
on your cases, Noble?

266
00:11:50,867 --> 00:11:52,233
Bok...

267
00:11:52,367 --> 00:11:54,067
you're acting like an OIC, huh.

268
00:11:55,733 --> 00:11:57,300
It's not like that.

269
00:11:57,433 --> 00:12:01,167
Of course, we've been distracted
these past few weeks.

270
00:12:01,300 --> 00:12:03,667
I just want us to focus again.

271
00:12:03,800 --> 00:12:05,700
We should focus.

272
00:12:05,833 --> 00:12:08,733
No one will be distracted, okay?

273
00:12:08,867 --> 00:12:09,867
Sir Eric!

274
00:12:10,000 --> 00:12:11,167
I brought you food.

275
00:12:11,300 --> 00:12:12,567
Selena...

276
00:12:13,633 --> 00:12:15,033
What a surprise.

277
00:12:15,200 --> 00:12:16,967
Huh? What surprise?

278
00:12:17,100 --> 00:12:20,133
You're the one who told me
to bring you food.

279
00:12:20,267 --> 00:12:22,500
Then you mentioned that,

280
00:12:22,633 --> 00:12:23,733
